description: From the verb phrase flame out.

entries.meaning: The act of flaming out or burning out; extinguishing.
(figurative) The act of quitting or failing, especially due to overwork or in a dramatic manner.
examples: The company was one of Silicon Valley's more famous dot-com flameouts.

entries.meaning: The sudden extinguishing of the flame of a burner (due to obstruction of fuel or airflow).
examples: The left engine suffered a flameout from ingesting heavy rain.
